window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>Emerson Grove is supposed to be my fresh start—a chance at a new beginning and a better future—yet my past is a force I never saw coming. </b></p> <p>Now, my head and my heart are at odds, my future is unknown, and everything I thought I knew is in disarray. Jameson, Ezra, Leo, and Jagger are ghosts from a different time, a different me. One night changed everything and I’m not the girl they once knew.</p> <p>But how can things go back to the way they were? With secrets, lies, and half-truths unfolding around me, I don’t know who to trust. The threats we once knew have grown and I’m still being kept in the dark.</p> <p>It seems we aren’t out of the trailer park after all. We’re just dealing with bigger issues in bigger houses. I refuse to stand by and watch my life morph uncontrollably around me. I’m torn and confused, but I’m Luella Carter, and I’m ready to fight.</p> <p><i>Watch Me Rise</i> is book two in the Emerson U Series. Scenes may be triggering to some, with violence and explicit sex scenes included.</p>"; 
